				\begin{document}$$ ORFscore={ \log}_2\left(\left({\sum}_{i=1}^3\frac{{\left(Fi-\overline{F}\right)}^2}{\overline{F}}\right)\kern.2em +1\right)\times \Big\{\kern1em \begin{array}{c}-1 if{F}_1>{F}_2\cup {F}_3>{F}_2\kern1em \\ {}\kern1em 1 otherwise\kern1em \end{array} $$\end{document}ORFscore=log2((∑i=13(Fi−F¯)2F¯)+1)×{−1ifF1>F2∪F3>F21otherwise. Fi are the number of reads on position i of the codon. With our offset calibration the 2nd position of a codon (i = 2) typically accumulates the majority of reads. Codons that accumulate more than 70 % of the footprints of an ORF were as in [14] ignored.
